In this article, President Biden speaks about his conversation with Tyre Nichols' mother, expressing his condolences and discussing his plans to push for the passage of the George Floyd Act. He emphasizes the need to control the violence and protests in a peaceful manner. The President mentions that Tyre Nichols' mother called for peaceful protests and no violence. He expresses his concern about the potential for violence but believes that the mother's plea is strong. The President also talks about his own experience with loss and assures the mother that the pain will eventually turn into fond memories. He emphasizes that innocent lives are at stake and the image of America is also impacted by how the situation is handled.